# SONET / SDH Abbreviations and Expansions

## SONET / SDH – Basic Abbreviations
- **SONET** – Synchronous Optical Network  
- **SDH** – Synchronous Digital Hierarchy  
- **STS** – Synchronous Transport Signal  
- **OC** – Optical Carrier  

## Level Abbreviations
- **STS-1** – Synchronous Transport Signal level 1  
- **STS-n** – n × STS-1 (electrical signal)  

- **OC-1** – Optical Carrier level 1  
- **OC-n** – n × OC-1 (optical signal)  

- **STM-1** – Synchronous Transport Module level 1  
- **STM-n** – n × STM-1 (SDH level)  

## SONET Frame Fields
- **PCI** – Physical Layer Control Information  
- **POH** – Path Overhead  
- **LOH** – Line Overhead  
- **SOH** – Section Overhead  

## Timing and Multiplexing
- **TDM** – Time Division Multiplexing  
- **VLSI** – Very Large Scale Integration  

## Data Rate Units
- **Mb/s** – Megabit per second  
- **Gb/s** – Gigabit per second  

---
*Short note:* SONET and SDH are different names for the same technology.  
SONET is mainly used in the USA, while SDH is used in Europe and worldwide.
